# Reproduction of an STM32F4 RTC crash on date/time register changes.
#
# The STM32F4_RTC model applies writes to the time/date registers field-by-field. 
# While the firmware writes the whole 32-bit register in one store, 
# Renode runs each field write callback sequentially, which can produce 
# a temporarily invalid DateTime (e.g. day-of-month 0 when setting a day divisible 
# by 10), throwing ArgumentOutOfRangeException and crashing the simulation.

using sysbus

mach create "stm32f4"
machine LoadPlatformDescription @platforms/cpus/stm32f4.repl
